<h2>Welcome</h2>

<p>Welcome to <a href="http://www.scouttrax.org/">ScoutTrax.org</a>
, an innovative scout tracking tool with features you
won't find together in any other scout tracking software. ScoutTrax.org was created
by software professionals who do this for free because they are passionate
about scouting.</p>

<h4>ScoutTrax.org is: </h4>
<h5>Simple and free, one-click tracking.</h5>

 <ul type=circle>
  <li >View a scout's complete record on a single page. </li>
  <li >Don't worry about whether the next unit or sponsoring
      organization will continue to pay for the program. It is free and will
      stay free. </li>
 </ul>

<h5>Accessible to scouts, parents and leaders on the web,
all the time.</h5>

 <ul type=circle>
  <li>ScoutTrax.org gives the power to the scout and his parents
      to be more involved with his progress. </li>
  <li>Lost handbook?No worries. The online
      record is safe and permanent. <i>Note:</i>ScoutTrax.org is not designed to replace
      all the information in the handbooks.  It is, however, a secure and efficient way to track progress
      and save records.)Like the BSA, we recommend that a physical copy of all scout records be kept. 
      </li>
  <li>ScoutTrax.org keeps track of information not included in
      the handbooks, like requirements for belt loops, pins, and religious emblems.</li>
 </ul>

<h5>Facilitates communication between scouts, parents and
leaders.</h5>

 <ul type=circle>
  <li>Leaders can email any or all members of their
      unit from one simple location to remind them of upcoming events.</li>
  <li>Leaders, parents and scouts all have access to their records and provide checks and balances for entered data. </li>
  <li>When a leader or parent signs off a requirement, the
      record is viewable by both leaders and parents, updated in real time.</li>
  <li>When a record is updated an email automatically
      notifies the parent.</li>
</ul>
<h5>Safe, Secure and Private </h5>


<ul type=circle>
  <li>Data is kept safe by regular offsite data backups. </li>
  <li>Privacy is protected by encrypted passwords and other
      security measures. </li>
</ul>

