<h5>Create a ScoutTrax.org account </h5>

 <ul type=circle>
  <li>Any scout leader may register
from the home page of ScoutTrax.org. Enter information including state, city,
council, charter organization, group, unit type, and unit number. Drop-down
menus will help you along the way. If
you register as a troop, each scout you add to the records will, by
default, be added to the troop. This can
easily be changed if you wish to create records for other unit types. Continue
to the next screen until registration is complete.</li>

<li>To complete account activation,
check your email for a link from ScoutTrax.org. 
By clicking on this link, you will automatically be sent to the "Unit
Management" page. Now you are ready to add
scouts. </li>

<li>Click on "Add Scout" and enter
information for each scout in your unit.</li>

<li>If you have not added all the scouts
in your unit, invite other leaders to add their scouts'
information. You can do this from the same
"Unit Management" page (see below). When
they respond to the invite, ScoutTrax.org will recognize them as being in the same
unit as you. This way all scouts in your unit can be viewed by any leader as
needed. Also, when a scout advances
to another unit, his records are already viewable by his new leaders.</li>
</ul>
